result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (5th or 6th) and Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) was dismissed by the court.

  • Paula L Eckert was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Defendant Paula L Eckert in court with Attorney Jamie J LaVora.  Lucas Paul Bennewitz appeared for the State of Wisconsin. This case has been renumbered to a felony case number now (Defendant pled guilty to Case #14CT1880 earlier today), therefore this case is now charged as a 5th offense.  Defendant waives his/her right to a Preliminary Hearing.  Bound over. Information filed.  Reading is waived.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count #2 on 3rd amended criminal complaint filed today.  Court performs plea colloquy and finds Defendant guilty of Count #2.  Count #1 is dismissed and read-in.  Count #3 is dismissed by operation of law.  State gives sentencing recommendations. Attorney LaVora requests Defendant's son's vehicle (Chevy Trailblazer) be exempt from IID.  Defendant was co-signer for loan on vehicle.  Court grants requst. Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following: 

COUNT #2:  IMPOSED SENTENCE:   

42 MONTHS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - 7 days)    **CONSECUTIVE TO 14CT1880**
  -  18 MONTHS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  24 MONTHS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

*D/L REVOCATION: 36 months.
*IGNITION INTERLOCK: 36 months.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
*No to operate a motor vehicle without a valid driver's license 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done 

BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $35.00  (to be paid as a condition of extended supervision- to be forward to Waukesha County Sheriff's Department);

FINE:  $2,658.00 & $250.00 DNA surcharge (to be paid out of cash bail posted and remainder due as a condition of extended supervision;

Defendant is not eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
